com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles

Class IconLabelStyle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.graph.styles.IconLabelStyle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ILabelStyle, ICloneable, Cloneable

    public class IconLabelStyle
extends Object
implements ILabelStyle, Cloneable
    A label style that draws an icon in addition to the text.

    This style draws the icon at the location specified by IconPlacement and delegates the drawing of the label's text to the Wrapped style.

      • getIconPlacement

        public final ILabelModelParameter getIconPlacement()
        Gets the parameter that specifies the icon placement.

        All valid node label model parameters can be used. The label's layout will be interpreted as the a node's layout and the icon will be placed relative to that layout as if it was a node's label.

        The default value is ExteriorLabelModel.WEST.

        Throws:
        NullPointerException - value is null.
        Returns:
        The icon placement parameter.
        See Also:
        setIconPlacement(ILabelModelParameter)

      • getWrapped

        public final ILabelStyle getWrapped()
        Gets the style that renders the text of the label.

        This style will be rendered before the icon and is responsible for rendering the Text, since IconLabelStyleRenderer will only render the Icon.

        The default value is DefaultLabelStyle.

        Throws:
        NullPointerException - value is null.
        Returns:
        The style that renders the text of the label.
        See Also:
        setWrapped(ILabelStyle)

      • getWrappedInsets

        public final InsetsD getWrappedInsets()
        Gets the insets that should be applied for the layout of the wrapped style rendering.

        The IconLabelStyleRenderer.getPreferredSize(com.yworks.yfiles.graph.ILabel, ILabelStyle) will take the preferred size of the Wrapped's ILabelStyleRenderer and add these insets to it. During the rendering these insets will be used to offset the rendering of the wrapped style.

        The default insets are empty.

        Returns:
        The insets for the wrapped style rendering.
        See Also:
        setWrappedInsets(InsetsD)
